Balıkesir Saat Kulesi - Balıkesir

Saat Kulesi 1829 yılında Girit’li Mehmet Paşa tarafından İstanbul Galata Kulesi’nin benzeri olarak silindir şeklinde yaptırılmış idi. 1897 yılındaki deprem nedeniyle yıkılınca, 1901 yılında bugünkü şekliyle yeniden yaptırılmıştır. Kare prizma şeklindeki bina, beyaz kesme taş ile yapılmış ve kabartma işçiliklerle de süslü hale getirilmiştir.En üst kat kubbe ile örtülmüş ve büyük bir çan eklenmiştir. Buranın hemen altındaki katta ise dört yöne de birer saat konmuştur.

Bu kadar değerli bir eserin bu kadar biçimsiz bir noktada kalması kötü olmuş. Kuleyi yapanlar ileriyi görememişler. Kilise çanı benzeri her saat başı çalması müslüman mahallesinde salyangoza benziyor bu ses değişmeli
Şehire ayrı bir hava katan mimari yapı. Ne zaman çan başlasa içimden pink floyd high hopes mırıldanmama sebep oluyor..o nedenle ayrı seviyorum.
Kültürel mirasımızın emanet ettiği güzel yapılardan birisi
Sunnyside is an amazing park, I was there for the Coca Cola Classic Disc Golf Tournament. Awesome weekend.
Loved the park with the rolling hills and trees. Had a wonderful firepit and frisbee golf
Nice relaxing place to picnic or just chill and listen to nature.
Nice quiet place to camp without the noise. Secluded and safe
Nice playground equipment, lots of shade trees, not much traffic. Nice place to have a picnic and play.

Absolutely scrumptious pastries. I am a fiend for coffee and a sweet treat to start of my morning. I came here multiple mornings throughout our visit to Des Moines.

Their pecan scones were phenomenal. I even got a loaf of their sprouted sourdough bread for the ride. Amazing place.

I had been staying up the street at a local establishment and decided to forego the boring, greasy, continental breakfast. After scouring reviews for eateries in walking distance? Decided to try Scenic Route Bakery and am extremely happy that I did! 
If ever you should find yourself in Des Moines? Wherever you might be lodging. Scenic Route is worth it. The pastries were wonderful and the house blend coffee I chose? The Honey Bee was perfect for my palate. I'd be hard pressed to have any desire to stop anywhere else when I'm back in Des Moines again.

Cheers!

I cannot say enough good things about this place!!! I was looking for a lesser-known, cute cafe to settle in and read my book while I sipped a hot drink. Scenic Route Bakery was everything I hoped for and MORE! Nice selection of pastries, plus some light lunch fare (get the chicken salad - it is ginormous and oh-so-delicious!). And the place is huge! It was constantly busy but I never felt crowded. It was cozy yet modern. They had something for everyone. I WILL be back! This is my new "spot" to get away from it all.
Delicious pastries and coffee. Great spot for meeting a friend to catch up or a casual business meeting. Friendly staff and great location.
The best croissants in town. Perfectly flakey and buttery.
